    {
      "name": "Authentic Mapo Tofu",
      "instructions": [
        "Cut the silken tofu into 2cm cubes and blanch in hot, lightly salted water for 1-2 minutes to firm up, then drain gently.",
        "Heat oil in a wok over medium heat. Add the minced beef and fry until browned and crispy, releasing its fat.",
        "Add the finely minced garlic and ginger, along with the Pixian Doubanjiang. Stir-fry until the oil turns red and fragrant.",
        "Pour in the chicken stock (or water), light soy sauce, and Shaoxing rice wine. Bring to a simmer.",
        "Gently slide in the blanched tofu cubes. Simmer for 3-5 minutes on low heat so the tofu absorbs the flavors.",
        "Drizzle in the cornstarch slurry in 2-3 stages to thicken the sauce until it clings to the tofu.",
        "Transfer to a serving bowl, sprinkle generously with freshly ground Sichuan peppercorn powder and chopped green onions, and drizzle with chili oil."
      ],
