      "name": "Gong Bao Ji Ding (Authentic Kung Pao Chicken)",
      "instructions": [
        "Cut the chicken breasts into 1.5cm cubes. Marinate with a pinch of salt, 1 tsp light soy sauce, 1 tsp Shaoxing rice wine, and 1 tsp cornstarch.",
        "Prepare the sweet and savory sauce by mixing Chinkiang vinegar, sugar, remaining light soy sauce, dark soy sauce, cornstarch, and 1 tbsp water in a small bowl.",
        "Cut the spring onions into 1.5cm segments, separating the white and green parts. Finely slice the garlic and ginger.",
        "Heat cooking oil in a wok over medium-low heat. Add Sichuan peppercorns and dried red chilies, stirring until fragrant and the chilies turn slightly dark.",
        "Increase heat to high, add the garlic, ginger, and the white segments of the spring onions, stirring quickly.",
        "Add the marinated chicken cubes and stir-fry rapidly until they turn opaque and are cooked through.",
        "Give the sauce mixture a quick stir, then pour it into the wok. Stir-fry constantly as the sauce thickens and glazes the chicken.",
        "Toss in the roasted peanuts and the remaining green spring onion segments, mix well, and serve immediately."
